ferences":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"هاد","root":"هدي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40975","n41399","n41500","n41501","n44268"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be Jewish","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"قُلْ يَٰأَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ هَادُوا إِنْ زَعَمْتُمْ أَنَّكُمْ أَوْلِيَاءُ لِلَّه مِنْ دُونِ ٱلنَّاسِ فَتَمَنَّوُا ٱلْمَوْتَ إِنْ كُنْتُمْ صَادِقِينَ","english":"Say, \"O you who are Jews, if you claim that you out of all of Man are God's allies then wish for death, if you should be truthful.\""}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn; to repent","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"وَٱكْتُبْ لَنَا فِي هَٰذِهِ ٱلدُّنْيَا حَسَنَةً وَفِي ٱلْآخِرَةِ إِنَّا هُدْنَا إِلَيْكَ","english":"And ordain for us good in this world and in the Hereafter, surely we have turned to You."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of هَدَى (hadā): guiding; guide","tags":["active","form-of","participle"],"examples":[{"text":"وَيَقُولُ ٱلَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا لَوْلَا أُنْزِلَ عَلَيْهِ آيَةٌ مِنْ رَبِّهِ إِنَّمَا أَنْتَ مُنْذِرٌ وَلِكُلِّ قَوْمٍ هَادٍ","english":"And those who disbelieved say, \"Why has a sign not been sent down to him from his Lord?\" You are only a warner, and for every people is a guide."},{"text":"أَلَيْسَ اللَّهُ بِكَافٍ عَبْدَهُ وَيُخَوِّفُونَكَ بِٱلَّذِينَ مِنْ دُونِهِ وَمَنْ يُضْلِلِ اللَّهُ فَمَا لَهُ مِنْ هَادٍ","english":"Is not Allah sufficient for His Servant [Prophet Muhammad]? And [yet], they threaten you with those [they worship] other than Him. And whoever Allah leaves astray - for him there is no guide."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of هُود (hūd, “Jews”, collective), as if from the root ه و د (h w d) related to returning, or from reanalysis of the noun يَهُود (yahūd, “Jews, Jewry”, collective) as a third-person masculine singular verb.\n\nDerived from the active participle of هَدَى (hadā, “to guide”)"},"ipa":["/haː.da/","/haː.din/"]}